Police in Benue State have killed four suspected bandits in Ukum council of the state. Weapons  recovered from them included  one Ak47 rifle, a G3 rifle, a locally-made pistol and assorted ammunition as well as charms. Briefing newsmen at Command headquarters in Makurdi, Commissioner of police Wale Abass said the bandits were killed by his men during an operation. CP Abbass said the bandits were ambushed and killed while on their way to attack a village called Gbagire in Ukum council.   Owo chief murder: police deny arrest of suspects     Lagos halts illegal construction of petrol station     Gunmen abduct two mourners in Delta   He said the operation was successful  because all their calls were tracked and carefully monitored by the intelligence unit. Governor Samuel Ortom commended the police, Inspector-General and the police commissioner in the state command for their effort. CP Abbas pledged that the command would do everything possible to keep the state safe. The bodies of the four  bandits were displayed at the Police command headquarters in Makurdi. Recovered weapons and  charms were also seen beside  their bodies.